# Line endings. This repo deploys to Linux containers, and two things break if a
# file arrives with CRLF:
#
#  - Migration .sql: the migrate runner checksums the file (sha256, matching
#    Prisma). CRLF vs LF is a different checksum, so a migration applied from a
#    Windows checkout (autocrlf=true) and re-checked by a Linux image mismatch,
#    and the drift guard rejects the deploy.
#  - Shell scripts: a `\r` in the shebang or a command fails in the container.
#
# Force LF for both, in the working tree and the blob, on every platform.
*.sql text eol=lf
*.sh  text eol=lf

# Everything else: normalize to LF in the repo, let git pick the working-tree
# ending per platform.
* text=auto
